Two people died in a North Coast road accident involving a car and a truck in the early hours of Friday morning.At approximately 00H15 on 07 July 2017, Netcare 911 responded to reports of a fatal collision on the North Coast Road westbound near Effingham Road in the Red Hill area, Durban.Eyewitnesses alleged that the car lost control and crashed into a truck that was parked in the forecourt of a petrol station. The exact details of the incident and preceding events will form part of a police investigation.Netcare 911 and paramedics from other private and provincial services, police and Fire &#038; Rescue crews all responded to the incident.Paramedics found that there had been the significant crash which had left two people dead, one other was in a critical condition and was placed on a ventilator at the scene and other had sustained moderate to serious injuries. The injured were attended to by Advanced Life Support paramedics and stabilized at the scene before being transported to a hospital for further urgent medical intervention.Some of the victims were trapped in the mangled wreck of the car and Fire Fighters used the Jaws of Life to remove the roof to access the victims and also move twisted metal away from the victims to free them. Source: Arrive Alive